public void visit(AeActivityIfDef aDef)
Visit the if activity. Note that in 1.1, the if activity is really a switch activity. We model it this way in order to have a single model for both 2.0 and 1.1.

visit

public void visit(AeIfDef aDef)
Visits the ifDef to write out its state. Note that the ifDef in bpel 1.1 is really the first case in a switch. We model it as an ifDef in order to have a single model for both 1.1 and 2.0.
